sudo apt-get update
go to elastic search download page and copy the link address from DEV
then do a wget on this copied address
then dpkg -i elastic-1.11.db or related that has been downloaded
installed in /usr/share/elasticsearch
go to bin and elasticsearch is here
then run by doing ./elasticsearch
then on you can use postman or curl to do a http://localhost:9200
to test this
note: the configuration files are in /etc/elasticsearch
in the yml files


